===Noun phrase===
'''pulmonary embolism'''

# {{pathology}} The [[embolism]] or obstruction of a pulmonary artery, usually by a detached blood clot from a leg or pelvic vein, which causes a stoppage of blood into the [[lung|lungs]]; symptoms include shortness of breath, chest pain, fainting, and sometimes death.
 
====Abbreviation====
*PE

